 great fitting helmet is critical to comfort and safety the current standard is to measure head circumference but that approach has serious limitations consider two rooms with a circumference of ’ while the rooms share the same circumference they have markedly different dimensions one measures ’ x ’ while the other measures ’ x ’ human head anatomy is also variable the same circumference could yield scores of different head lengths and breadths traditional sizing approaches do not account for these differences the vicis axis fit system incorporates head length and breadth measurements to determine a player’s optimal helmet size informed by detailed head measurements of hundreds of current and former nfl and ncaa football players the axis fit system provides an anatomically correct fit based on the unique head shapes of elite athletes the zero offers  different sizing combinations eliminating the need for shims and air bladders taking comfort and safety to a new level after determining the player’s optimal helmet size with the axis fit system the zero’s two innermost layers provide additional protection and exceptional fit and comfort  configure the vicis zero is a highlyengineered football helmet designed to reduce impact forces it is the culmination of a year m research and development effort shaped by some of the world’s leading athletes engineers and neurosurgeons the zero’s multiple layers work together to slow impact forces the helmet features a soft outer shell and an underlying layer of columns designed to mitigate collisions from multiple directions the zero delivers breakthroughs in safety based on current state of the art testing protocols it also elevates performance featuring the industry’s widest ﬁeld of peripheral view and low aerodynamic drag our tagline is protect the athleteelevate the game® – and that’s what we’ve done with the zero note the zero was designed for use by elite athletes and is recommended for players weighing over  lbs we expect to serve smaller lighter athletes with future helmet models designed for their size and level of play a helmet’s foremost job is protection vicis engineers and neurosurgeons have developed a multilayered highlyengineered helmet design that mitigates linear and rotational impact forces the lode shell®absorbs impact load by locally deforming like a car bumper automotive safety engineers have used local deformation to protect people for decades we’re the first to bring this proven innovation to football helmets vicis rflx®employs a highlyengineered columnar structure that moves omnidirectionally to reduce linear and rotational forces the columnar geometry used in our rflx layer is based on principles first described by leonhard euler a swiss physicist in the sthe lode shell and rflx layer work together to reduce impact forces leveraging well established engineering principles and materials longused in stringent aerospace and automotive applications tested to withstand multiple seasons of play the vicis zero delivers st century innovation built on bedrock scientific principles the arch shell®the axis fit system determines the relationship between head length and breadth measurements commonly called an “aspect ratio” for a player and facilitates selection of an appropriately sized arch shell there are  different arch shells available providing outstanding fit and additional protection the form liner®the form liner is designed to work in unison with the arch shell constructed of special foams and waterproof textiles the form liner conforms to the player’s unique head topography and distributes pressure uniformly around the head there are  different form liners available to enable unparalleled comfort and precise fit how it works the zero’s multiple layers work together to slow impact forces the helmet features a soft outer shell and an underlying layer of columns designed to mitigate collisions from multiple directions the zero reduces head impact severity better than any helmet on the market based on an algorithm developed for professional football to assess helmet performance this calculation incorporates both linear straightahead and rotational forces while others only consider linear impact performance supporting test results were generated by one of the leading biomechanics laboratories in north america onfield testimonials what do actual pro and college players think about the zero comfort and fit we used a datadriven approach to optimize fit below helmet pressure maps illustrate the zeros superior fit and comfort vs a leading competitor one of vicis’ founders is a neurosurgeon and some of the world’s preeminent neurosurgeons serve on the vicis council our scientiﬁc advisory board we have a deep understanding of head shape and anatomy we have incorporated feedback from these neurosurgeons and scores of elite football equipment managers to develop the vicis axis fit system® the vicis axis fit system incorporates head length and breadth measurements to determine a player’s optimal helmet size the zero oﬀers  diﬀerent sizing combinations eliminating the need for shims and air bladders and taking comfort and safety to a new level blue  low pressure red  high pressure head surface pressure observed with a vicis zero compared to a leading competitor during a  metersecond impact to the front of the helmet field of view fov the vicis zero provides a wider ﬁeld of view than traditional helmets in laboratory testing the zero was shown to oﬀer players a  degree ﬁeld of view nearly the maximum of human peripheral vision  degrees this is nearly  degrees more than the next best traditional helmet and  degrees more than another popular traditional helmet the sooner you see the sooner you can react  based on vicis rdi lab testing attention to detail because we designed the zero from scratch we examined every part of the helmet and manufacturing process looking for improvement opportunities our facemasks are argonwelded resulting in a cleaner weld our jaw pads are engineered for easy removal in the event of an emergency every detail matters even those you cannot see every vicis facemask is constructed from high grade titanium selected for its strength and weight properties traditional competitors weld their masks in the presence of room air which contains oxygen oxygen is detrimental to titanium we bathe our welds in argon gas to purge room air that may be present you can see the diﬀerence in our welds vicis argon oxygenated traditional competitors use velcro® or snap attachments to secure their jaw pads in an emergency situation calling for helmet removal the eﬀort to release these pads could place rotational pressure on the head our neurosurgeon advisors suggested we design our jaw pads diﬀerently allowing them to be removed with minimal rotational pressure as a result vicis jaw pads attach to the zero using cored titanium retention studs that can be fully released allowing the pads to be removed with straight and smooth motion the vicis zero configurator is optimized for modern browsers for the best experience please use the latest version of ie edge chrome firefox or safari if you have an older version of internet explorer and cannot use a newer version internet browser please call  between  am to  pm pt and we will be happy to assist you with your preorder the zero configurator is optimized for modern browsers for the best experience please use the latest version of ie edge chrome firefox or safari note the zero is designed for football players at the high school level and above if you are under  lbs andor will not play at the high school level or above next season please contact us at infovicisco to be notified of future helmet releases the zero is not currently available for purchase online vicis foundation the vicis foundation intends to donate zero helmets and other protective equipment to players and programs who may not otherwise have the means to benefit from this technology more information will follow in coming weeks learn more × sign up for vicis email with vicis huddle you can be the first to know about product releases development advancements and other vicis news email name placeholder sign up vicis inc  sebring  fl  company information products resources my account talk to a db advisor  business directory fl sebring business services nec business services at noncommercial site vicis inc v vicis inc claim this business  boney rd sebring fl  get directions   business info founded  incorporated annual revenue  employee count  industries business services at noncommercial site contacts michael flowers contact business your email address subject message send message company summary since  vicis inc has been providing business services at noncommercial site from sebring verified status unverified address unverified last verified  phone unverified payment method unverified view full report similar businesses nearby our similar businesses nearby shows similar businesses in their industry and region based on information found in their dun  bradstreet credibility review profile competitive landscape our competitive landscape shows how this business compares to similar businesses in their industry and region based on information found in their dun  bradstreet credibility review profile payments accepted no data hours sunday   monday   tuesday   wednesday   thursday   friday   saturday   v view additional data select from over  networks below to view available data about this business if this data is unavailable or inaccurate and you own or represent this business click here for more information on how you may be able to correct it credibility review google facebookcom yellowbookcom bingcom yellowpagescom merchantcircle tele atlas tomtom twittercom aol mapquest yahoo local applesiri groupon hotfrogcom comcastnet search reachlocal admedia dealsplus shoptopiacom alteryx dogtime media kslcom sirtune americantownscom driverside kudzucom specialsagentcom answerscom e